Jobs and higher education's market scenario 

Report on higher education fields & Job / internship market in India. Analysed datasets and statistics of students interests on different jobs and available jobs in respective jobs..
Report prepared and data analysed by Singaraju Shanmukha Kowshik.

Table of Contents

1.Problem Introduction
2. Dataset's 
3. Features and Processing
4. Results and Discussion
5. Conclusion
6. References

1. Problem Introduction

Currently there are lakhs of students are graduating each year in India.Each of them have a specific interest or goal they want to pursue .Most of the graduates want to become software engineers.
But how many jobs are available in market?
How many students choosing a specific course as their career choice?
What is the scenario of students that are graduating?
what are different career options after they graduate ?
What is the availability of jobs in a specific field ?

I directed my analysis in a way to answer above questions.

2. Data Sets

1) Students on their career choice 
                                                         what they want to do after graduation i.e Higher education or Employment Or internship.I gathered the information required to create the  dataset by circulating a Google Form throughout different colleges and asked students to mention their career choices . 

2) AICTE statistics on number of students

                                                I collected information regarding the number of students of different fields passing out each year from AICTE (MHRD).


3) Jobs list LinkedIn

                                   I scrapped LinkedIn website to get number of job postings and internships available in each field and created the dataset required.




3. Features and processing

Firstly I calculated the percentage of students pursuing different  career's such as Employment,Internship and Higher Education. After that on the basis on their career choices i divided that the dataset into 3 further parts on each i conducted the analysis.

For each of those 3 data sets i analysed percent of students choosing the following as their career intrest. 

    a. Software Development

    b. Data Analytics

    c. Data Science & Machine Learning

    d. Product Management

    e. UI UX Design

    f . Business Development (Sales) 


And then from the statistics of AICTE i estimated number of students pursuing the above choice as their carrer either by Jobs or internships or part time jobs for thoose who are doing Higher Education.

I compared the numbers i obtained above to the jobs dataset that i prepared from LinkedIn and visualised the result.

4.Result and Discussion

  Students Choosing Different Career Choices



People choosing Employment as the after choice of degree are 58.33 %

People choosing Higher Education as the after choice of degree are 34.52 %

People choosing Internship as the after choice of degree are 7.14 %


1) Students Choosing Employment as their Career Choice



                                    Percentage of students choosing Job as their career



According to MHRD and AICTE report there are 14,06,245 engineering students are graduate in year 2019-20 and 14,16,088 in 2018-19.

So an average of 14 lakh engineering students are graduting per year out of which 30% are belong to computer science (CSE,IT).

So 4.2 lakh (0.3x14L) computer science students are gradutaing per year.


            


                                                                 AICTE Statistics

By the percentage of students interested in each fields we calculated at starting we have 

    2.45 Lakh students are interested in doing job

    1.45 lakh students are interested in higher education

    0.3 lakh students are interested in Internships

 We have a total of 2.45 lakh students interested in doing jobs Lets find how many persons are interested in doing jobs in specific fields. And from analysis we conducted before we know the percent of students interested in each field.


There are 20.408% people are intrested in doing Data Science and Machine Learning jobs .So a total of 0.5 Lakh students are intrested in doing Data Science and Machine Learning job

There are 6.122% people are intrested in doing Business Development (Sales) jobs .So a total of 0.15 Lakh students are intrested in doing Business Development (Sales) job

There are 24.49% people are intrested in doing Software Development jobs .So a total of 0.6 Lakh students are intrested in doing Software Development job

There are 4.082% people are intrested in doing Data Analyst jobs .So a total of 0.1 Lakh students are intrested in doing Data Analyst job

There are 2.041% people are intrested in doing Product Management jobs .So a total of 0.05 Lakh students are intrested in doing Product Management job

There are 6.122% people are intrested in doing UI UX Design jobs .So a total of 0.15 Lakh students are intrested in doing UI UX Design job

There are 36.735% people are intrested in doing Other jobs .So a total of 0.9 Lakh students are intrested in doing Other job.


And Jobs available for each feild in LinkedIn are

'Software Development': 30503,

'Data Analyst': 6218,

'Data Science and Machine Learning': 2579,

'Product Management': 9966,'

'UI UX Design': 2502,

'Business Development (Sales)': 14787


                                                                   Market Gap for Jobs


As we can see jobs required and available are almost same in the field of Business Development.

Whereas Required jobs are less than available jobs in Product Management. So there are less students showing interest towards Product Management even though there are many jobs.

As for all the other fields available jobs are much less than required jobs.So there will be a heavy competition for students to get that job.

We can see a huge Market Gap in  the field Data Science and Machine Learning . This is due to increase in recent popularity for data science.

                            Percent of Students choosing to do internship after their Graduation



We have a total of 0.3 lakh students interested in doing jobs Lets find how many persons are intrested in doing jobs in specific fields.

There are 0.0% people are intrested in doing Business Development (Sales) jobs .So a total of 0.0 Lakh students are intrested in doing Business Development (Sales) job

                                                            MARKET GAP FOR INTERNSHIPS

Even though it kinda seems like a lot of difference , but these are the interns that are available in LinkedIn. There can be some off site interns,some that are provided by institutes etc..
But we can see that students that are opting for interns show comparatively less interest in Business Development and Data Analysis fields.



3) Students Choosing Higher Education as their Career Choice

As for students intrested in higher educations part time jobs are available which helps them to earn while studying thereby decreasing economical burden on their families, introducing students to responsibilities and discipline.

We have a total of 1.45 lakh students intrested in doing jobs Lets find how many persons are intrested in doing jobs in specific fields



                            Percent of Students choosing different careers after their Higher Education

There are 13.793% people are intrested in doing Data Science and Machine Learning jobs .So a total of 0.338 Lakh students are intrested in doing Data Science and Machine Learning job
There are 3.448% people are intrested in doing Business Development (Sales) jobs .So a total of 0.084 Lakh students are intrested in doing Business Development (Sales) job
There are 24.138% people are intrested in doing Software Development jobs .So a total of 0.591 Lakh students are intrested in doing Software Development job
There are 6.897% people are intrested in doing Data Analyst jobs .So a total of 0.169 Lakh students are intrested in doing Data Analyst job
There are 3.448% people are intrested in doing Product Management jobs .So a total of 0.084 Lakh students are intrested in doing Product Management job
There are 0.0% people are intrested in doing UI UX Design jobs .So a total of 0.0 Lakh students are intrested in doing UI UX Design job
There are 48.276% people are intrested in doing Other jobs .So a total of 1.183 Lakh students are intrested in doing Other job

And the Part Time jobs available on LinkedIn are

        'Software Development': 56,

        'Data Analyst': 13,

        'Data Science and Machine Learning': 15,

        'Product Management': 23,

        'UI UX Design': 5,

        'Business Development (Sales)': 172


                                                         MARKET GAP FOR PART TIME JOBS


Even though it kinda seems like a lot of difference , but these are the part time jobs that are available in LinkedIn. There can be some off site interns,some that are provided by institutes in which we are doing our higher education etc..

And some of the students doing higher education in India are no that interested in doing jobs. So the market will be less than the market gap we are seeing here.

    5. Conclusion

So we analysed all the important factors and answered the question that we raised at the beginning.As we can see there is a huge market gap maybe in 10,000's in every where i.e jobs ,interns and part times.
As this is a survey conducted on small scale there is a chance of inaccuracy And we consider jobs only from LinkedIn. But there can be many more ways a student can get a job like placement or internship programs by college or attending off-campus interviews.
By considering all other factors with a proper data set the result can be accurate .Then market gap will most probably reduce from 10,000's to 1000's .
